    "body": "Technically it's feasible to nuke out the error and display empty coinbase address on screen. But personally I would refer to keep the current behavior, reject this API call in light mode and don't show the coinbase message at all.\r\n\r\n```\r\nWARN [03-11|13:42:54.553] Light client mode is an experimental feature \r\nWelcome to the Geth JavaScript console!\r\n\r\ninstance: Geth/v1.10.17-unstable/darwin-arm64/go1.17.3\r\ncoinbase: 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000\r\nat block: 0 (Thu Jan 01 1970 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (CST))\r\n datadir: /Users/mac/Library/Ethereum\r\n modules: admin:1.0 debug:1.0 eth:1.0 ethash:1.0 les:1.0 net:1.0 personal:1.0 rpc:1.0 txpool:1.0 vflux:1.0 web3:1.0\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlthough technically it's also feasible to avoid this call in the first place, but I think it's not worthwhile to add the complexity. So I would just close this issue.",
